issue.body:
**Original author :** Blatti Yves

With easySDI v4 we have lost a v2 feature:
*Customization on MAP colors for vector features.* (In V2 was present in easySDI SHOP, because it was the only map back then)

V2 parameters:
!easySDI_v2_shop_map_parameters.png!

Result in V2 JS:
```

OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['default']['fillColor'] = '#7EED18';
OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['default']['strokeColor'] = '#663300';
OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['default']['strokeWidth'] = '2';
OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['select']['fillColor'] = '#7EED18';
OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['select']['strokeColor'] = 'white';
OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['temporary']['fillColor'] = '#7EED18';
OpenLayers.Feature.Vector.style['temporary']['strokeColor'] = '#663300';
```


*This allows administrators to make a MAP match with site's template.*

We should add this back in the MAP parameters. (And use the "Joomla nice color picker":https://docs.joomla.org/Color_form_field_type ;-) )

**Fixed versions :** 4.3.2
